{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0001 — Monetary Amount Input Validation (ai-bookkeeper) — Decision + Implementation", "content": "## ADR 0001 — Input-boundary validation for monetary amounts\n**Status:** Accepted · 2026-05-27 · Area: `src/features/ledger`\n\n### Context\nAmounts are the ledger's core type but had **no validation boundary**. `Transaction.amount` is a plain signed `number` (`ledger/types.ts:8`) where **positive = income, negative = expense** — a convention `wealth-score/lib/compute.ts` and `lib/format.ts` already depend on. A `grep` of `src/` found only consumers, zero guards. Amounts enter today only via typed mock data (`data.ts`); the live SMS/OCR and Plaid adapters aren't built yet. So malformed input (negative magnitude, non-numeric OCR, sub-cent precision, `$58,000`→`5800000` range errors) would reach balances, tax reserves and the valuation with no signal.\n\n### Decision\nAdd a **pure-function validation boundary** — keep the `number` representation, validate at ingest.\n- `features/ledger/lib/amount.ts` — `parseAmount(raw, direction)` → `{ ok:true, value } | { ok:false, error }`. Coerces number/string (tolerates `$`, `,`, spaces); rejects empty, non-numeric, non-finite, **negative magnitude**, **zero**, **>2 decimals**, and magnitude **> $1,000,000**. Direction sets the sign. Plus `isValidSignedAmount()` (guards stored values) and `explainAmountError()` (user-facing SMS/review text).\n- `features/ledger/lib/ingest.ts` — `ingestTransaction`/`ingestTransactions` map a `RawTransaction` → canonical `Transaction`, partitioning into `accepted` / `rejected`. The single seam the future Twilio/OCR + Plaid adapters call.\n- Follows the repo's existing co-located pure-lib convention (`customers/lib/normalize.ts`), exported via the ledger barrel.\n\n**Alternative considered — integer cents:** the drift-proof fix, but a breaking change across every consumer for a still-mocked scaffold. **Deferred** to a follow-up ADR when Cloud SQL persistence lands; drift mitigated now by 2-decimal canonicalization + sub-cent rejection.\n\n### Consequences\n- One auditable boundary; typed rejection reasons instead of silent corruption; **no consumer changes** (representation unchanged); sign convention now codified, not just conventional.\n- Residual: amounts stay IEEE-754 floats — aggregate sub-cent drift remains until the cents migration. Bounded by the per-txn ceiling.\n- Verified: `tsc --noEmit` clean for new modules (one pre-existing unrelated e2e error); validator logic **12/12 boundary cases pass**.\n\n---\n### Task breakdown — 13 points total\n| # | Task | Scope | Points |\n|---|------|-------|--------|\n| 1 | Validation lib | `amount.ts` — `parseAmount`/`isValidSignedAmount`/`explainAmountError` | 3 ✅ done |\n| 2 | Ingest boundary | `ingest.ts` — single/batch raw→canonical with accept/reject partition | 2 ✅ done |\n| 3 | Barrel exports + ADR log | `ledger/index.ts`, `docs/adr/0001-*.md` | 1 ✅ done |\n| 4 | Wire unit-test runner | add `node:test`+`tsx` (or vitest) script & CI step; run `amount.test.ts` | 2 |\n| 5 | SMS/OCR adapter integration | Twilio→Gemini OCR path calls `ingestTransaction`; rejects → SMS reply via `explainAmountError` | 3 |\n| 6 | Plaid adapter integration | bank-feed sync calls `ingestTransactions`; route `rejected[]` to review queue | 2 |\n\nTasks 1–3 are **implemented and verified now**. Tasks 4–6 attach to adapters/test infra not yet in the repo and are scoped for the delivery agent (event `architecture.analysis.completed` emitted).", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

